# investigation-board-platform - Project Rules

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: READ THIS FIRST

This file is AUTOMATICALLY loaded at the start of EVERY conversation.
You MUST follow these rules WITHOUT being reminded.

---

## 🔄 MANDATORY WORKFLOW FOR EVERY CODE CHANGE

### AFTER EVERY CODE CHANGE, YOU MUST:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  POST-CHANGE CHECKLIST                       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                             │
│  1. □ Update VERSION file (semantic versioning)            │
│  2. □ Create changelog/vX.X.X.md with details              │
│  3. □ Update changelog/CHANGELOG.md with summary           │
│  4. □ Create git branch named vX.X.X                       │
│  5. □ Commit with message: "Release vX.X.X: description"   │
│  6. □ Push to GitHub: git push origin vX.X.X               │
│                                                             │
│  ⚠️ DO NOT SKIP ANY STEP!                                   │
│  ⚠️ DO NOT WAIT FOR USER REMINDER!                          │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## 📋 Version Numbering (Semantic Versioning)

| Change Type | Version Change | Example |
|-------------|----------------|---------|
| Bug fix | PATCH | 1.2.5 → 1.2.6 |
| New feature | MINOR | 1.2.6 → 1.3.0 |
| Breaking change | MAJOR | 1.3.0 → 2.0.0 |

---

## 🎨 Symbols for Changelog

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| 🔧 | Bug fix |
| ✨ | New feature |
| 🎨 | Design improvement |
| ⚡ | Performance improvement |
| 📝 | Documentation |
| 🟢 | New code added |
| 🔴 | Code removed |

---

## 🚀 Git Commands (COPY-PASTE READY)

```bash
# After making code changes:

# 1. Read current version
cat VERSION

# 2. Update VERSION (example: patch fix)
echo "1.7.2" > VERSION

# 3. Create branch
git checkout -b v1.7.2

# 4. Stage changes
git add .

# 5. Commit
git commit -m "Release v1.7.2: وصف التغيير"

# 6. Push
git push origin v1.7.2
```

---

## 📁 Files to Read at Session Start

When starting a new session or continuing, ALWAYS read:

1. `VERSION` - Current version number
2. `changelog/CHANGELOG.md` - Recent changes (last 50 lines)
3. Last `changelog/v*.md` file - Latest release details

---

## ⛔ NEVER DO THESE

- ❌ Commit directly to main branch
- ❌ Skip changelog documentation
- ❌ Forget to update VERSION
- ❌ Forget to push to GitHub
- ❌ Wait for user reminder

